Download and install the following software:

https://www.vagrantup.com/

https://www.virtualbox.org/

https://sliksvn.com/download/

After the initial installation of vagrant, run the following command:

vagrant plugin install vagrant-vbguest

After all installations are complete, run vagrant_initial_setup.bat to create your PostgreSQL VM.
Once set up is complete, connect to localhost in PGAdmin or Putty to access you database.

